
<div class="profileContainer">
	<div class="profileDesc" style="width: 100%; height: 272px;">
		<div class="name">Phillip Gay &ldquo;Andrew&rdquo;</div>
		<div class="bio">
			<p>Phillip Gay's acting career began with his appearance in a university stage production while an undergraduate at Case Western Reserve University. After receiving his Ph.D. in Sociology from Harvard University, he became a professor of sociology at San Diego State University.<br />
			<br />
			While at San Diego State, and eventually becoming chairperson of its sociology department, Phillip authored numerous books and articles dealing with sociologically relevant current events, as well as a murder-mystery novel (i.e. ACADEMIC AFFAIRS), a history of South Africa up until the end of apartheid (i.e. MODERN SOUTH AFRICA, McGraw-Hill, publisher) and a student-oriented book titled CONQUERING COLLEGE: THE MEANING OF SUCCESS), appeared in stage plays (e.g. WAIT UNTIL DARK, BAREFOOT IN THE PART, had small roles in short films, and also served on the Board of Director of the San Diego Playhouse in Encinitas, California.<br />
			<br />
			During his San Diego State years, Phillip also appeared on all the local (San Diego) news stations as a social commentator (also know as a "talking head"). Since leaving San Diego State University, and before MONSTER KILLER, Phillip has appeared in a few short films and commercial, and had a small role in Edgar Bravo's ONE HOUR FANTASY GIRL, and completed an as yet unbooked documentary film titled WHAT LOVE DOES. At present Phillip is devoting most of energies to jogging, daily yoga classes, and working on a sequel to his first murder-mystery novel.<br />
			</p>
		</div>			
	</div>
