	<div id="marc_maynon">
		<div class="name">Marc Maynon &ldquo;Mark&rdquo;</div>
		<div class="bio">
			<p>Marc was born in Brooklyn Coney Island, New York in 1987 the son of a protestant minister and a clinical social worker. The family left for California when Marc was 4 and a half. From a very early age Marc loved to sing and was very creative. In his early years, one could always find him drawing a picture, writing a story or even trying his luck at video game development. By the age of 14 he began acting in school musicals. At 21 he Graduated with a BA in musical theater from the Ray Bolger Musical Theater Program at UCLA and has been both acting and singing ever since. He is also a songwriter.
			</p>						
		</div>
	</div>
	<div id="katelynn_dubow">
		<div class="name">Katelynn Dubow &quot;Katherine&quot;</div>
		<div class="bio">
			<p>Katelynn was born in El Paso, Texas where she began performing and singing at 4 in school and local theatre. At 11 she got her first electric piano and has since learned to play songs by ear and write her own music.<br />
			<br />
			She began modeling at 16, participating in the regional show for the CW’s  Model Material where she placed top five. Katelynn soon thereafter moved to Los Angeles to pursue her passions for acting and singing where she has since has been in over 17 commercials and has over 3,000 subscribers to her YouTube channel.<br />
			<br />
			Her most recent film roles include the title/lead character in I LOVE A GIRL NAMED JENNY, Sophia in FORGIVE ME, Katherine in MONSTER KILLER. She has also been in music videos for Yellowcard, Disney's Austin and Ally, Tegan and Sara, the Script, and top You Tubers including Shane Dawson and more. 
			</p>		
		</div>										
	</div>
	<div id="tammie_smalls">
		<div class="name">Tammie Smalls &ldquo;Gloria&rdquo;</div>
		<div class="bio">
			<p>Tammie Smalls is an actor, comedic improviser/sketch performer and singer/songwriter. She has performed at Second City LA, iO West, UCB, and at numerous comedy festivals throughout the United States.<br />
 			<br />
			She recently appeared in the comedic dance film BIG BREAKIN’ directed by Mattio Martinez, several webisodes of COLLEGE HUMOR directed by Matt Pollock, and the dramatic sci-fi thriller MONSTER KILLER directed by Edgar Michael Bravo. She also appears as herself in the critically acclaimed documentary, DARK GIRLS.<br /> 
			<br />
			A life long athlete, Tammie is known for very physical, body-bending, risk-taking performances. She is currently working on an album and solo show which she incorporates her original characters, original songs, and her unique brand of goofiness.<br />
			<br />
			Tammie was born and raised in Schenectady, New York and arrived in Los Angeles via New York City. She’s the youngest of three children in a super-talented family!
			</p>								
		</div>
	</div>
	<div id="bryan_hurd">
		<div class="name">Bryan Hurd &ldquo;Frank&rdquo;</div>
		<div class="bio">
			<p>Bryan has been acting since 1978 starting with regional theater were he was nominated for Best Supporting Actor for his work in the Sacramento Regional Theater Production of 'Don't Drink the Water'.<br />
			<br /> 
			Dinner theater throughout Northern California provided training for his sojourn in the San Francisco Bay Area in the 80's where he also performed stand-up comedy and trained with The Spaghetti Jam Improv group while touring with two other troupes. Bryan received Shakespearian training with Patrick Godfrey of the Royal Shakespeare in London, appearing in Merry Wives, Love's Labour's, Othello, Midsummer's, and many other of the Bard's plays.<br />
			<br /> 
			Bryan landed prominent roles in commercials, independent films, theater and improv in the Northern California area before coming to Los Angeles in 2005. MONSTER KILLER is his most recent on screen performance. As his heart will always remain in theater, his current production is 'References to Salvador Dali Make Me Hot'.<br />
			<br /> 
			Some of Bryan's greatest times were had making two films with No Restrictions Entertainment.</p>		
		</div>										
	</div>
	<div id="paul_robert_walsh">
		<div class="name">Paul Robert (Kevin) Walsh &ldquo;The Old Man&rdquo;</div>
		<div class="bio">
			<p>Paul Robert (Kevin) Walsh was born in New York and moved to Washington, D.C. where he played piano in rhythm and blues bands as a kid. He returned to New York and was featured as a background actor in two Andy Warhol films that starred Nico. Kevin later traveled to California in 1967 where he continued to play music.<br />
			<br /> 
			In 2010, Kevin began working in commercials, TV, film and music videos. He played the role of the Record Producer in the Saint Motel music video, “Benny Goodman”, and was featured as an older version of Tom O’Dell in Tom O’Dell’s “Grow Old With Me”. Most recently, Kevin was privileged for the opportunity to play the role of The Old Man in MONSTER KILLER. 
			</p>	
		</div>											
	</div>
